Package gameboard.objects

Class MovingObject

java.lang.Object
gameboard.objects.MovingObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
Farmer, Machine, WorkingDevice
public class MovingObject
extends java.lang.Object
This class represents any object on the gameboard, that is able to move.
Author:
Luisaibele, Judith

  • Field Summary

    Fields
    Modifier and Type Field Description
    private java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> places
    an array list that represents all the indexes of the tiles on the gameboard that are no passable (calculated: y * 30 + x)
    private boolean selected
    boolean that saves if the moving object is selected at the moment
    private int x
    the column on which the moving object is standing
    private int y
    the row on which the moving object is standing

      Constructor to set each param and to reload the game.

      x - the x-value to which the object is set on the matchfield

      selected - sets whether the object is selected or not

    • proofPassabilty

      public boolean proofPassabilty​(int x, int y)
      This method checks, if it's possible to move to the next tile. Therefore, it uses the array list with not passable tiles that holds all the indexes, that are not passable.
      Parameters:
      x - x-value of the tile that the player wants to move to
      y - y-value of the tile that the player wants to move to
      Returns:
      if it's possible to move to the next tile

    • moveRight

      public void moveRight​(GameScene gameScene) throws MovingException
      This method represents the functionality of each object to move right.
      Parameters:
      gameScene - the GameScene object of the actual game
      Throws:
      MovingException - It's not possible to move off the gameboard. If the player tries this method throws an exception.
